#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "Administration by using transactional updates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:28
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&slema; was designed to use the read-only root file system. So after the "
"deployment is complete, you are not able to perform direct modifications to "
"the root file system, e.g. by using <command>zypper</command> . The concept "
"of transactional updates has been implemented to enable you to modify and "
"keep your system up to date."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Transactional updates key features are the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"they are atomic - the update is applied only if it completes successfully."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:42
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"changes are applied in a separate snapshot and thus they do not influence "
"the running system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "they provide easy rollback."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:53
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each time you call the <command>transactional-update</command> to change "
"your system&mdash;either to install a package, perform an update or apply a "
"patch; the following actions take place:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "Modifying the root file system"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A new read-write snapshot is created from your current root file system or "
"from a snapshot that you specified."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "All changes are applied (update, patches or package installation)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:69
#, no-c-format
msgid "The snapshot is switched back to the read-only mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The new root file system snapshot is prepared to be applied after reboot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After rebooting the new root file system is used instead of the current root "
"file system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Bear in mind that without rebooting your system, the changes won't be "
"applied."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:90
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you do not reboot your machine before performing further changes to "
"the file system, the new snapshot are created always from the current root. "
"You will end up with several parallel snapshots, each spanshots includes the "
"particular change, but not changes from the other snapshots. After reboot, "
"the last created snapshot will be used as your current root file system and "
"will not include changes done in the previous snapshots."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:99
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>transactional-update</command> usage"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:100
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>transactional-update</command> command enables atomic "
"installation or removal of updates; updates are applied only if all of them "
"can be successfully installed. <command>transactional-update</command> "
"creates a snapshot of your system before the update is applied, and you can "
"restore this snapshot. All changes become active only after reboot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>transactional-update</command> command syntax is the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"transactional-update <option>[option]</option> <replaceable>[general "
"command]</replaceable> <replaceable>[package command]</replaceable> "
"<replaceable>standalone command</replaceable>\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "Running <command>transactional-update</command> without arguments."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you do not specify any command or option while running the "
"<command>transactional-update</command> command, the system updates itself."
msgstr ""

