msgid ""
"The snapshots with the set <literal>number</literal> cleanup algorithm will "
"be deleted according to rules configured in <filename>/etc/snapper/configs/"
"root</filename> by the following parameters:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:553
#, no-c-format
msgid "NUMBER_MIN_AGE"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:555
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines the minimum age of a snapshot in seconds that can be automatically "
"removed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:561
#, no-c-format
msgid "NUMBER_LIMIT/NUMBER_LIMIT_IMPORTANT"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:563
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines the maximim count of stored snapshots. The cleaning algorithms "
"delete snapshots above the specified maximum value, without taking the "
"snapshot and file system space into account. The algorithms also delete "
"snapshots above the minimum value until the limits for the snapshot and file "
"system are reached."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:572
#, no-c-format
msgid "System rollback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:573
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"GRUB 2 enables to boot from btrfs snapshots and thus allows you to use any "
"older functional snapshot in case the new snapshot is corrupted."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:576
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When booting a snapshot, the parts of the file system included in the "
"snapshot are mounted read-only; all other file systems and parts that are "
"excluded from snapshots are mounted read-write and can be modified."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:580
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rolling back to a specific installation state"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:581
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An initial bootable snapshot is created at the end of the initial system "
"installation. You can go back to that state at any time by booting this "
"snapshot. The snapshot can be identified by the description <literal>after "
"installation</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:588
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are two methods how you can perform a system rollback."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:593
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From a running system you can set the default snapshot, see more in <xref "
"linkend=\"proc-running-snapshot\" xrefstyle=\"template:Combustion\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:598
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Especially in cases where the current snapshot is broken, you can boot to "
"the new snapshot and set it then default, for details refer to <xref linkend="
"\"proc-boot-snapshot\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:603
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case your current snapshot is functional, you can use the following "
"procedure for system rollback."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:608
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choose the snapshot that should be set as default, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:611
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"  &prompt.root;transactional-update status\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:614
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"to get a list of available snapshots. Note the number of the snapshot to be "
"set as default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:619
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the snapshot as the default by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"  &prompt.root;transactional-update rollback <replaceable>snapshot number</"
"replaceable>\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:625
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you omit the <replaceable>snapshot number</replaceable> , the current "
"snapshot will be set as default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:630
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reboot your system to boot in to the new default snapshot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:635
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following procedure is used in case, the current snapshot is broken and "
"you are not able to boot into it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:640
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reboot your system and select <literal>Start bootloader from a read-only "
"snapshot</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:645
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose a snapshot to boot. The snapshots are sorted according to the date of "
"creation, the latest being the top one."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:650
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Log in to your system and check whether everything works as expected. Bear "
"in mind that the snapshot directories are read-only, so you cannot write "
"into them. Data written to directories excluded from the snapshots will stay "
"untouched."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:655
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the snapshot you booted into is not suitable for rollback, reboot your "
"system and choose another one."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:658
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the snapshot works as expected, you can perform rollback by running the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:661
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"   &prompt.root; <command>transactional-update rollback</command>\n"
"   "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:664
#, no-c-format
msgid "And reboot afterwards."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:672
#, no-c-format
msgid "Managing automatic transactional updates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:673
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Automatic updates are controlled by a <command>systemd.timer</command> that "
"runs once per day. This applies all updates, and informs "
"<command>rebootmgrd</command> that the machine should be rebooted. You may "
"adjust the time when the update runs, see systemd.timer(5). To adjust the "
"maintenance window, which is when <command>rebootmgrd</command> reboots the "
"system, see rebootmgrd(8)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:681
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can disable automatic transactional updates with this command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>systemctl --now disable transactional-update.timer</"
"command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:692
#, no-c-format
msgid "Snapshots"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:694
#, no-c-format
msgid "Snapshots are mandatory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:695
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As snapshots are crucial for &slema; correct functioning, do not disable the "
"feature and ensure that the root partition is big enough to store the "
"snapshots."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:699
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a snapshot is created, both the snapshot and the original point to the "
"same blocks in the file system. So, initially a snapshot does not occupy "
"additional disk space. If data in the original file system is modified, "
"changed data blocks are copied while the old data blocks are kept for the "
"snapshot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:702
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Snapshots always reside on the same partition or subvolume on which the "
"snapshot has been taken. It is not possible to store snapshots on a "
"different partition or subvolume. As a result, partitions containing "
"snapshots need to be larger than partitions not containing snapshots. The "
"exact amount depends strongly on the number of snapshots you keep and the "
"amount of data modifications. As a rule of thumb, give partitions twice as "
"much space as you normally would. To prevent disks from running out of "
"space, old snapshots are automatically cleaned up."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:705
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Snapshot that are known to be working properly are marked as "
"<emphasis>important</emphasis> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:711
#, no-c-format
msgid "Directories excluded from snapshots"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:712
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As some directories store user specific or volatile data, these directories "
"are excluded from snapshots:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:717
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/home</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:719
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Contains user's data. To avoid overwriting this data, this directory is "
"excluded from snapshots."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:725
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/root</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:732
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/opt</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:734
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Third-party products usually get installed to <filename>/opt</filename> . It "
"is excluded to avoid uninstalling these applications on rollbacks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:740
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/srv</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:742
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Contains data for Web and FTP servers. It is excluded to avoid data loss on "
"rollbacks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:748
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/usr/local</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:750
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This directory is used when manually installing software. It is excluded to "
"avoid uninstalling these installations on rollbacks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:756
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/var</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:758
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This directory contains many variable files, including logs, temporary "
"caches, third party products in <filename>/var/opt</filename> , and is the "
"default location for virtual machine images and databases. Therefore this "
"subvolume is created to exclude all of this variable data from snapshots and "
"has Copy-On-Write disabled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:764
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/tmp</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:766
#, no-c-format
msgid "The directory contains temporal data."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:772
#, no-c-format
msgid "the architecture specific <filename>/boot/grub2</filename> directory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:774
#, no-c-format
msgid "A rollback of the boot loader binaries is not supported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:783
#, no-c-format
msgid "Showing exclusive disk space used by snapshots"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:784
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Snapshots share data, for efficient use of storage space, so using ordinary "
"commands like <command>du</command> and <command>df</command> won't measure "
"used disk space accurately. When you want to free up disk space on Btrfs "
"with quotas enabled, you need to know how much exclusive disk space is used "
"by each snapshot, rather than shared space. The <command>btrfs</command> "
"command provides a view of space used by snapshots:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:792
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&prompt.root;btrfs qgroup show -p /\n"
"qgroupid         rfer         excl parent  \n"
"--------         ----         ---- ------  \n"
"0/5          16.00KiB     16.00KiB ---     \n"
"[...]    \n"
"0/272         3.09GiB     14.23MiB 1/0     \n"
"0/273         3.11GiB    144.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/274         3.11GiB    112.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/275         3.11GiB    128.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/276         3.11GiB     80.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/277         3.11GiB    256.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/278         3.11GiB    112.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/279         3.12GiB     64.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/280         3.12GiB     16.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"1/0           3.33GiB    222.95MiB --- \n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:809
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>qgroupid</literal> column displays the identification number "
"for each subvolume, assigning a qgroup level/ID combination."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:813
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>rfer</literal> column displays the total amount of data "
"referred to in the subvolume."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:817
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>excl</literal> column displays the exclusive data in each "
"subvolume."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:821
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>parent</literal> column shows the parent qgroup of the "
"subvolumes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:824
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The final item, <literal>1/0</literal> , shows the totals for the parent "
"qgroup. In the above example, 222.95 MiB will be freed if all subvolumes are "
"removed. Run the following command to see which snapshots are associated "
"with each subvolume:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:834
#, no-c-format
msgid "Health checker"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:835
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Health checker is a program delivered with &slema; that during booting of "
"your system checks whether services are running properly."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:838
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During the boot process <literal>systemd</literal> calls Health checker that "
"calls its plugins. Each plugin checks a particular service or condition. If "
"each check passes, a status file&mdash; <filename>/var/lib/misc/health-"
"checker.state</filename> is created. The status file marks the current root "
"file system correct."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:840
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If any of the health checker plugins reports an error, the action taken "
"depends on a particular condition as described below:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:845
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>The snapshot is booted for the first time.</emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:847
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the current snapshot is different from the last one that worked properly, "
"an automatic rollback to the last working snapshot is performed. This means "
"that the last change performed to the file system broke the snapshot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:853
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>The snapshot has already booted correctly in the past.</emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:855
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There coud be just a temporary problem, the system is rebooted automatically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:861
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>The reboot of a previously correctly booted snapshot has failed.</"
"emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:863
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If there already was a problem during boot and automatic reboot has been "
"triggered but the problem still persists, the system is kept running to "
"enable to the admnistration to fix the problem. The services that are tested "
"by the healtch checker plugins are stopped if possible."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:870
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding customer plugins"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:871
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Health checker enables you to add your plugins to check services during the "
"booting process. Each plugin is a bash script that must fulfill the "
"following requirements:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:876
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The plugins are located within a secific directory&mdash; <filename>/usr/"
"libexec/health-checker</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:881
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The service that will be checked by the particular plugin must be defined in "
"the <filename>/usr/lib/systemd/system/health-checker.service</filename> file "
"in the <literal>Unit</literal> section. For example, the <literal>etcd</"
"literal> service is defined as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:884
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" [Unit]\n"
" ...\n"
" After=etcd.service\n"
" ...\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:892
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each plugin has the <literal>run.checks</literal> and "
"<literal>stop_services</literal> functions defined. The <literal>run.checks</"
"literal> function checks whether a particular service has started properly. "
"Bear in mind that service that has not been enabled by systemd, should be "
"ignored. The function <literal>stop_services</literal> is called in case a "
"service has not been started properly to stop the particular service. You "
"can use the plugin template for your reference."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:901
#, no-c-format
msgid "&slema; administration by using Cockpit"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:902
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Cockpit is a web-based graphical interface that enables you to manage your "
"&slema; deployment in one place. Cockpit is a standard delivery in case of "
"raw images, or can be installed in case of the manual installation, for the "
"installation process refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-settings-software\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:905
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before running Cockpit on you machine, you need to enable the cockpit socket "
"in systemd by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:908
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" &prompt.root;systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:912
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you have enabled the firewall, you also must open the firewall for "
"Cockpit as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:915
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" &prompt.root;firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-service=cockpit\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:918
#, no-c-format
msgid "And then reload the firewall configuration by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:921
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" &prompt.root;firewall-cmd --reload\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:925
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can access the Cockpit web interface by opening the following "
"address in your web browser:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:928
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" https://ip-address-of-machine:9090\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:931
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A login screen opens. To login, use the same credentials as you use to login "
"to your machine via console or SSH."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:945
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After successful login, an overview of your machine opens. Here you can view "
"and/or administrate your system performance, network interfaces, Podman "
"containers, services, logs or you can access your machine by using a shell "
"terminal."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:949
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cockpit login screen"
msgstr ""
